			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yet another one!
<br />

<br />
*EDIT - Forgot to metion* - Adventure group in Miragul's Menagerie, set out to assassinate a boss mob. Actual Dungeon was one of the ice caverns and not Miragul's lab. I forget the actual name.
<br />

<br />
Total time in the zone was 47 min 21 seconds (2841 seconds). According to EQCompanion our combat uptime (for our warrior tank at least) was 30 min 32 seconds (1832). Approximately 64.4% combat uptime from first zone in to final zone out. Typical pulls were in 3s or 4s.
<br />

<br />
Group consisted of:
<br />
Splitstone - Level 65 warrior, pre-Elemental gear
<br />
Tanolena - Level 65 rogue, pre-Elemental gear
<br />
Darck - Level 65 enchanter, Elemental gear
<br />
Alandrea - Level 65 druid, Elemental gear (and Darck bot)
<br />
Existence - Level 65 cleric, Elemental gear
<br />
Xalmat - Level 65 mage, mostly Elemental gear
<br />

<br />
Pets were Epic pet Xasn, and Enchanter pets Xasantik and Gartik. Both Darck and Existence were highly melee oriented i might add  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
All casters had FT15, MC3, and max mana regen available without a bard or beastlord.
<br />

<br />
I'll post four figures here. First figure is total damage. Second figure is DPS as output by EQCompanion (obviously going to be skewed, but some will be curious anyway). Third figure is DPS according to our uptime (1832 sec). Fourth figure is DPS for total time in the zone.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Splitstone</span> (Warrior)
<br />
Total Damage: 116,020
<br />
EQCompanion DPS: 63.33
<br />
Uptime DPS: 63.33
<br />
Total DPS: 40.84
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Tanolena</span> (Rogue)
<br />
Total Damage: 163,118
<br />
EQCompanion DPS: 95.88
<br />
