				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, this is from MM hard mode, Slaughter mission (59 mobs).
<br />
Grp was: (all non ep gear)
<br />

<br />
Me 65 Mage  
<br />
65 Paladin
<br />
65 Enchanter 
<br />
65 Cleric  65 Ranger
<br />
65 Wizard 
<br />

<br />
We finished this zone with 2 mins on clock, had to stop and rez the chanter a few times (but she saved our azzs enough).
<br />

<br />
OK Ranger was doing DPS logs, i only have the combined dps not a break down,
<br />

<br />
Iuar including pets : 492k damage
<br />
Ranger: 471648 
<br />
Wizard: 421676
<br />
Paladin: 362224
<br />

<br />
What surprised me here was the sheer amount of damage done. I had been rodding my grp when rods were done (canni'ing back up when lom), doing ds's etc.
<br />
My pet of choice was 61 Air fully equiped.
<br />
I used all my AA's as they popped on mobs for added dps.
<br />
Over the whole Adventure, including downtime (rezzing, canni etc) i think (if i worked it right) my DPS was 89.3.
<br />

<br />
LDoN is great for mages as we have great burst and extended damage potential. We also have the ability to OT/DS/Rod as well as see whats ahead. LDoN has provided Mages an opportunity to shine in grps who may not usually want to grp a Mage. 
<br />
All i can say is this has been a great expansion so far (helps that i'm on a PvP server also, so the wayfarer camps are fun  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="Twisted Evil" border="0" /> ).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
